  "tool": "propose",
  "gene_genome": {
    "biological_question": "Determine how synaptic gene-expression programs vary across identified neural circuit connections at nanoscale resolution.",
    "sample_context": "Fixed brain tissue sections or cleared neural circuit preparations with labeled pre- and postsynaptic populations.",
    "core_method": "Expansion microscopy combined with multiplexed RNA detection and circuit-specific synaptic labeling.",
    "molecular_targets": "Multiplexed RNA panels enriched for synaptic, plasticity-related, cell-type-specific, and activity-regulated transcripts.",
    "spatial_scale": "Synapse-resolved nanoscale localization of RNA relative to pre- and postsynaptic markers after tissue expansion.",
    "validation_strategy": "Validate transcript localization against smFISH, immunostaining for synaptic proteins, known cell-type markers, and perturbations of neural activity or synaptic plasticity."
  }
}
```

[result]

```json
{
  "proposed_child": {
    "status": "generated",
    "summary": "A synapse-focused expansion-multiplexed RNA method for nanoscale mapping of gene expression across neural circuits.",
    "expected_extension": "Moves from general expanded-tissue transcriptomics to circuit- and synapse-resolved multiplex RNA profiling."
  }
}
```

