    "study_context": "Protected areas and community-managed landscapes facing biodiversity pressure, with emphasis on co-managed territories where local and indigenous knowledge can guide interpretation of ecological change.",
    "methods": "Develop a participatory multimodal fusion pipeline that aligns satellite foundation-model embeddings with local sensor observations and indigenous ecological indicators; use temporal anomaly detection, weak supervision, knowledge-guided feature weighting, and uncertainty-aware biodiversity risk mapping.",
    "evaluation": "Compare satellite-only foundation-model baselines against multimodal fusion models using early-warning lead time, biodiversity-loss detection accuracy, false-alarm rates, spatial generalization, community validation, and usefulness for local conservation decisions.",
    "contribution": "Provides a co-produced AI framework for biodiversity early warning that extends conservation AI from generic remote sensing analysis toward culturally grounded, locally validated, and sensor-enriched monitoring."
  }
}
```

